<subSubSection id="C3496520B148C06EFF62FC7D4783C02A" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB148C06EFF62FC7D423AC33D" blockId="5.[151,504,978,1042]" box="[151,295,1015,1042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
(
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFF6AFC7D4202C33D" box="[159,287,1015,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Figs 29–36</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB148C06EFF62FBB547FCC101" blockId="5.[151,1437,1087,1905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B148C06EFF62FBB5426AC377" box="[151,375,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body uniformly brown (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFD6AFBB541EBC376" box="[671,758,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); antennal segment I dark brown, II pale, II–IV yellow but shaded at extreme apex of III and distal third of IV, V–IX brown (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFC86FBE940DAC352" box="[883,967,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
); fore wings with a long longitudinal dark band, pale at subbase and apex, claves brown (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFD69FB0D41F3C38E" box="[668,750,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); all legs brown, with the base of hind tibiae pale. Head wider than long, sculptured with closely transverse striae; postocular setae in two rows but irregularly arranged (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFAC9FB21468DC3EA" box="[1340,1424,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palp segment II subdivided (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFDBBFB4541BCC3C6" box="[590,673,1230,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Antennal segments III–IV sensorium vermicular and around apex, with internal markings (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFE5EFB79411DC222" box="[427,512,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Pronotum wider than long, sculptured with transverse striae, with about 40–50 discal setae and 3 pairs of posteromarginal setae slightly shorter than discal setae, except S2 stouter. Mesonotum with closely transverse striate, with a few wrinkles between sculpture lines on posterior part; lateral and posteromedian setae short and stout; anteromedian CPS absent (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFD33FAD54000C256" box="[710,797,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Metascutum sculpture with internal markings between sculpture lines, anterior-medially with closely transverse striae, posterior area with reticulation, median and submedian pairs of setae situated near middle, submedian pair slightly behind, CPS present (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFB9BFA2D47DCC2EE" box="[1134,1217,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergite I with transverse lines, II-VIII smooth medially, VI-VIII with lateral transverse lines weakly. Sternites II–VI with 3–4 pairs of posteromarginal setae, VII with 5 pairs of posteromarginal setae in front of posterior margin, 2 pairs of accessory setae between S1 and S2; Sternites V–VIII each with 1–4 pairs of discal setae (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB148C06EFB75F99947C9C101" box="[1152,1236,1555,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Aduncothrips kailiensis sp.n. (29) Body of female; (30) Head and pronotum; (31) Forewing; (32) Meso and metanotum; (33) Antennal segments III–IV; (34) Antenna; (35) Maxillary palp; (36) Hemisternite VIII (arrows indicate discal setae on hemisternites)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB148C06EFF32F9BD43A7C1B6" blockId="5.[151,1437,1087,1905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B148C06EFF32F9BD426BC17E" bold="true" box="[199,374,1591,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Measurements</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54E88809B148C06EFE73F9BD42F7C17E" box="[390,490,1591,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
in microns). Body length 1753; head length 141, width 188. Pronotum length 171, width 210. Fore wing length 754, median width 111. Antennal segments I–IX length: 56, 50, 81, 83, 60, 48, 34, 16, 15.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB148C06EFF32F9294299C193" blockId="5.[151,1437,1087,1905]" box="[199,388,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
